Within the course, basic knowledge of the historical background, value system, theoretical and practical approaches of social work is acquired. Levels and methods of social work and opportunities for self-care and professional development are also discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  As a result of completing the subject, the learner acquires basic social work knowledge through a historical, theoretical and philosophical perspective and a systematic approach to the regulations and terminology of the field, which is the basis for the following specialities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows the development history of social protection and welfare; 2) knows the most important social risks and opportunities for their prevention and mitigation; 3) knows the basic goals, methods, levels, target groups and funding schemes of social work; 4) knows the ethical principles and value system of social work; 5) knows the most important regulations and sources of information in the social field; 6) understands the importance of self-care and professional development
